From d19c541d269eddd9702b687fd4ba587c7da497a2 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Marc Zyngier <maz@kernel.org>
Date: Wed, 13 Aug 2025 17:37:47 +0100
Subject: [PATCH] KVM: arm64: Correctly populate FAR_EL2 on nested SEA
 injection

References: vera-baremetal.txt git-fixes
Patch-mainline: v6.17-rc4
Git-commit: d19c541d269eddd9702b687fd4ba587c7da497a2

vcpu_write_sys_reg()'s signature is not totally obvious, and it
is rather easy to write something that looks correct, except that...
Oh wait...

Swap addr and FAR_EL2 to restore some sanity in the nested SEA
department.

Fixes: 9aba641b9ec2a ("KVM: arm64: nv: Respect exception routing rules for SEAs")
Signed-off-by: Marc Zyngier <maz@kernel.org>
Link: https://lore.kernel.org/r/20250813163747.2591317-1-maz@kernel.org
Signed-off-by: Oliver Upton <oliver.upton@linux.dev>
Acked-by: Michal Suchanek <msuchanek@suse.de>
---
 arch/arm64/kvm/emulate-nested.c |    2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

--- a/arch/arm64/kvm/emulate-nested.c
+++ b/arch/arm64/kvm/emulate-nested.c
@@ -2630,6 +2630,6 @@ int kvm_inject_nested_sea(struct kvm_vcp
 			     iabt ? ESR_ELx_EC_IABT_LOW : ESR_ELx_EC_DABT_LOW);
 	esr |= ESR_ELx_FSC_EXTABT | ESR_ELx_IL;
 
-	vcpu_write_sys_reg(vcpu, FAR_EL2, addr);
+	vcpu_write_sys_reg(vcpu, addr, FAR_EL2);
 	return kvm_inject_nested_sync(vcpu, esr);
 }
